The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

Life

 Costume call

 What: 

 Exhibition of costume jewellery by Soumyas Creation.

 Where: The store at 57/9 Ballygunge Circular Road.

 When: July 1 to 7, 10 am to 8.30 pm.

 Take a look: The weeklong exhibition offers a wide variety of jewellery that is a mish mash of traditional and contemporary patterns.

 On display will be plaited and corded costume jewellery with hand-painted beads, Swarovski crystals and old coins.

 Some come studded with semi-precious stones like amethysts, sapphires, tourmaline, rubilites, blue topaz, peridots and citrines. 

 A full range with antique-finish silver beads and coloured glass beads throw up trendy buys to go with western wear.

 Also on offer will be silver chains 

 and pearl-studded ornaments. These are suitable picks to 

 go with regular and party wear.

 A special attraction is a select range of jewellery with dramatic tribal motifs. 

 You can also choose from thewa jewellery with intricate detailing made by master craftsmen.

 Pocket pinch: Prices start as low as Rs 10 and go up to a few thousands.

 Voiceover: The range we are showcasing this time is very wide, with lots of innovations. The designs are a mix of traditional and trendy motifs. Theres something to suit all occasions and all kinds of outfits, says Sudatta Chakroborty from Soumyas Creation.




